Package: bc-seek
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Parallel hardware-saturating file search CLI
 Walks directory trees in parallel with a lock-free MPMC queue and
 per-worker growable output buffers. Supports find(1)-style
 predicates (--name, --type, --size, --mtime, --newer, --perm,
 --max-depth, --min-depth), fd(1)-style defaults (hidden and
 common build directories pruned unless --hidden / --no-ignore),
 null-separated output, and an adaptive parallel / mono dispatch.
 .
 On warm-cache corpora (~1M files), typically 5x-9x faster than
 find(1) and 5%-38% faster than fd(1), thanks to stat-lazy
 predicate evaluation and per-worker contention-free accumulation.
